3. “Tap to talk” pulsing ring
Turn the central flower into a clear interactive trigger with a soft pulse ring.

xml
<button class="tap-to-talk">
    <span class="pulse-ring"></span>
    <span class="inner-circle">
        <!-- flower/petal element goes here -->
    </span>
</button>
css
.tap-to-talk {
position: relative;
border: none;
background: transparent;
cursor: pointer;
}
.tap-to-talk .inner-circle {
position: relative;
z-index: 2;
width: 80px;
height: 80px;
border-radius: 50%;
background: #ffffff;
display: flex;
align-items: center;
justify-content: center;
}
.tap-to-talk .pulse-ring {
position: absolute;
inset: -10px;
border-radius: 50%;
border: 2px solid rgba(107, 75, 255, 0.5); /* purple */
animation: pulseRing 2s ease-out infinite;
z-index: 1;
}
@keyframes pulseRing {
0% {
transform: scale(0.8);
opacity: 0.8;
}
100% {
transform: scale(1.4);
opacity: 0;
}
}
You can further tie the ring intensity to the states:

Idle: slow, low‑opacity pulse.

Listening: faster pulse.

Speaking: thicker border or dual rings.

